      • getProperties

        public List<Properties> getProperties()
        Gets the value of the properties property. <p> This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a <CODE>set</CODE> method for the properties property. <p> For example, to add a new item, do as follows: <pre> getProperties().add(newItem); </pre> <p> Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list Properties
